modules.description: This module implements the U2F protocol for two-factor authentication using public key cryptography. It provides functions to generate registration and authentication challenges, verify client responses, and handle errors during these operations. The core data types include challenges, key handles, public keys, and certificates, which are used to securely register and authenticate hardware tokens. Concrete use cases involve creating a U2F state with an application ID, initiating registration with existing key handles, and validating authentication responses with user presence and counter checks.
